data.title: Paula Cole returns with new album for Museum of Making Music concert today

data.text:
Paula Cole may still not know where all the cowboys have gone, to invoke the title of her 1997 breakthrough hit.

But she knows exactly where many classic American songs are to be found.

And she features 20 of them on her eighth studio album, “Ballads,” due out Aug. 11.

They include such gems as Billie Holiday’s “God Bless the Child,” John Coltrane’s “Naima” and Bob Dylan’s “The Lonesome Death of Hattie Carroll,” along with songs popularized by Nina Simone, Ella Fitzgerald, Bobbie Gentry and more.

You can expect to hear a live preview of at least part of Cole’s new album when she performs tonight, Thursday, July 6, at Carlsbad’s Museum of Making Music.

Paula Cole: 7 p.m. today. Museum of Making Music, 5790 Armada Drive, Carlsbad. $25. (760) 438-5996 or museumofmakingmusic.org
